MBOMBELA – A man was arrested last night for attempted murder and firing a firearm in a municipal area. Police spokesman Lt Col Erhard Stroh said a detective that was in the street at the time, spotted the suspect assaulting a man. “The man started running away from the suspect and he chased after him. He shot twice in the direction of the victim but missed.” The suspect was arrested at the scene by the police. ” The firearm was found on the man and it was licenced.” Stroh said Rob Ferreira hospital confirmed the victim had not sustained any gunshot wounds. The victim is set to be on the way to recovery. Divergent Ops, SAPS, and Hi-Tech Security responded to the scene.  Divergent Ops Jacques Meiring said they had assisted in securing the scene. 